WEBVTT

00:06.270 --> 00:08.067
- WHOO!

00:08.100 --> 00:09.101
YES!

00:09.140 --> 00:11.631
* UH-HUH UH-HUH

00:11.670 --> 00:13.069
I CANNOT BE DEFEATED.

00:13.110 --> 00:15.476
WHO ELSE WANTS SOME?

00:15.510 --> 00:16.704
-IDO.

00:16.750 --> 00:19.275
- WHY CAN'T I EVER BEAT HIM?

00:19.320 --> 00:20.719
- 'CAUSE YOU GOT NO GAME, GUS.

00:20.750 --> 00:23.048
I'D STICK TO TAPPING.
BALL UP.

00:23.090 --> 00:26.218
ALL RIGHT, SHAWN,
FIRST ONE TO 11 WINS.

00:26.260 --> 00:28.080
- HOW MUCH ARE YOU
SPOTI'ING ME?

00:28.120 --> 00:29.587
- NOTHING.
WINNERS DON'T NEED SPOTS.

00:29.630 --> 00:31.518
YOU KNOW WHAT THEY NEED?
- STEROIDS.

00:31.560 --> 00:32.697
- NOBODY'S USING THAT STUFF,
GUS.

00:32.730 --> 00:34.595
THAT'S JUST A RUMOR.

00:34.630 --> 00:36.393
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT THEY NEED,
SHAWN.

00:36.430 --> 00:38.694
THEY NEED TO BELIEVE THAT THEY
CAN BE VICTORIOUS

00:38.730 --> 00:41.130
NO MATTER HOW TOUGH
THE CHALLENGE.

00:41.170 --> 00:43.707
NOW...

00:43.740 --> 00:47.278
START BELIEVING.

00:58.490 --> 01:00.458
GET THAT WEAK-ASS CRAP
OUT OF MY FACE!

01:00.490 --> 01:01.616
THIS IS MY HOUSE!

01:01.660 --> 01:05.778
- TECH NICALLY,
IT'S THE BANK'S.

01:05.830 --> 01:07.718
- YOU'RE NEVER GONNA
IMPROVE IN LIFE

01:07.760 --> 01:09.728
IF YOU KEEP COMPETING
WITH PEOPLE WHO STINK.

01:09.770 --> 01:11.829
NO OFFENSE, GUS.
- NONE TAKEN.

01:11.870 --> 01:13.667
- YOU'VE GOT
TO CHALLENGE YOURSELF.

01:13.700 --> 01:16.601
IF YOU DON'T,
COMPLACENCY SETS IN.

01:16.640 --> 01:21.430
AND BAD THINGS HAPPEN
WHEN WE BECOME COMPLACENT.

01:26.650 --> 01:29.346
- "IF YOU TELL ANYONE
MY SECRET, EDEN,

01:29.390 --> 01:31.187
"MY CAREER WILL BE OVER.

01:31.220 --> 01:33.757
WE WILL BE OVER,"
SAID CHASE.

01:33.790 --> 01:36.884
EDEN REPLIED, "I'D DIE BEFORE
I'D TELL ANYONE

01:36.930 --> 01:39.751
YOU'RE A SHAPESHIFI'ER,
DOCTOR."

01:39.800 --> 01:44.169
IF ONLY EDEN KNEW HOW PROPHETIC
THOSE WORDS WOULD BE.

01:44.200 --> 01:46.168
[electronic beep]
END OF DISC FIVE

01:46.200 --> 01:47.792
OF INTERNITY.

01:47.840 --> 01:49.831
[cell phone rings]

01:53.880 --> 01:56.644
- LOOK, THERE'S A REASON THOSE
BOOKS HAVE SOLD

01:56.680 --> 01:58.307
ALMOST 30 MILLION COPIES,
GUS.

01:58.350 --> 01:59.669
- MOSTLY TO TEENAGE GIRLS.

01:59.720 --> 02:01.847
- AND ADULT MALES WHO ENJOY
READING STORIES

02:01.880 --> 02:04.713
ABOUT VAMPIRE DOCTORS AND THEIR
DYSFUNCTIONAL DATING LIVES.

02:04.750 --> 02:06.581
- [scoffs]
- YOU'RE ONE TO TALK,

02:06.620 --> 02:09.623
MR. "I BOUGHT WIN A DATE
WITH TAD HAMILTON ON DVD."

02:09.660 --> 02:11.628
- THERE WERE 15 DELETED SCENES,
SHAWN.

02:11.660 --> 02:13.525
15.

02:13.560 --> 02:15.198
YOU SAID YOU WERE GOING
TO THE OFFICE LAST NIGHT

02:15.230 --> 02:16.561
TO CATCH UP ON WORK.

02:16.600 --> 02:18.465
- WHICH I DID, THEN I SAW
THOSE BEERS IN THE FRIDGE.

02:18.500 --> 02:19.637
- OUR FRIDGE DOESN'T WORK.

02:19.670 --> 02:20.932
- YES, BUT 7-11'S DOES.

02:20.970 --> 02:23.939
IT IS THERE THAT I SAW THE
INTERNITY AUDIOBOOKS FOR SALE

02:23.970 --> 02:26.837
AND DECIDED THAT THE PAPERWORK
WOULD HAVE TO WAIT.

02:26.880 --> 02:28.700
HEY, HOW'D YOUR DATE GO
WITH THAT CHICK

02:28.740 --> 02:29.638
WHO SPELLS HER NAME WEIRD?

02:29.680 --> 02:32.547
- HER NAME IS KIM
AND SHE SPELLS IT K-I-M.

02:32.580 --> 02:33.740
- WHICH IS JUST OBNOXIOUS.

02:33.780 --> 02:35.839
IT'S LIKE IF I WAS "SHAWN"
WITH THREE SS.

02:35.880 --> 02:37.848
- YOU'RE JUST JEALOUS
'CAUSE I'M IN A RELATIONSHIP.

02:37.890 --> 02:39.687
- PLEASE.
YOU'VE KNOWN HER FOR SIX DAYS.

02:39.720 --> 02:41.449
- WHICH HAVE BEEN PURE MAGIC.

02:41.490 --> 02:42.525
YOU KNOW WHEN YOU JUST KNOW?

02:42.560 --> 02:44.755
- GREAT.
YOU GUYS.

02:44.790 --> 02:46.724
- WELL, GOOD MORNING
TO YOU TOO, MINKA.

02:46.760 --> 02:47.829
GUS WILL HAVE HIS USUAL.

02:47.860 --> 02:49.862
- SIX CHOCOLATE CHIP MUFFINS
AND A CHOCOLATE MILK.

02:49.900 --> 02:51.492
- EXTRA CHOCOLATE-Y.

02:51.530 --> 02:52.929
- I'LL TAKE DOWN A BAKED GOOD
THAT I WILL

02:52.970 --> 02:54.790
BE CHOOSING MOMENTARILY
AND A LATI'E

02:56.710 --> 02:59.304
ONCE I NAIL THE TRIVIA QUESTION
THAT YOU PUT ON THAT BOARD

02:59.340 --> 03:01.274
JUST LIKE I DO EVERY MORNING.

03:01.310 --> 03:02.948
- OH, EXCEPT THIS ONE.

03:02.980 --> 03:05.471
- I'M AFRAID YOUR CONFIDENCE
REEKS FALSER

03:05.510 --> 03:06.716
THAN YOUR BOYFRIEND'S I.D.,

03:06.750 --> 03:10.709
WHICH, FYI, I SAW TAPED
TO THE COUNTER AT 7-11.

03:10.750 --> 03:11.819
GOOD LUCK TO YOU.

03:11.850 --> 03:13.784
- WAIT TILL YOU GET A CHANCE

03:13.820 --> 03:15.549
TO MEET KIM AT THE WEDDING
ON SATURDAY.

03:15.590 --> 03:16.852
YOU ARE GOING TO LOVE HER.

03:16.890 --> 03:18.881
- IF YOU THINK THAT I'M GONNA
BE A THIRD WHEEL

03:18.930 --> 03:21.751
TO YOU AND KIM WITH ONE "I,"
THEN YOU'RE NUTS.

03:21.800 --> 03:23.768
I'M BRINGING MY OWN DATE.
- WHO?

03:23.800 --> 03:25.791
- I'LL GIVE YOU A HINT.
IT RHYMES WITH "GOO-LIET."

03:25.830 --> 03:26.637
- JULIET?

03:26.670 --> 03:27.489
- YOU NAILED IT
ON THE FIRST GUESS.

03:27.540 --> 03:29.758
THAT'S TIGHT.
- WHEN DID YOU ASK HER?

03:29.810 --> 03:31.266
- I HAVEN'T YET.
I'M NOT WORRIED.

03:31.310 --> 03:32.675
IT'S A LOCK
SHE'LL SAY, "YES."

03:32.710 --> 03:33.836
- HOW DO YOU KNOW?

03:33.880 --> 03:35.507
- "A," SHE HAS
NO PLANS THAT NIGHT.

03:35.540 --> 03:37.644
"B," THERE'S ALWAYS BEEN
A SORT OF UNSPOKEN,

03:37.680 --> 03:39.739
SOMETIMES SPOKEN THING
BETWEEN THE TWO OF US.

03:39.780 --> 03:42.817
AND, FOUR, I HAPPEN TO KNOW
SHE LOVES SPONTANEITY.

03:42.850 --> 03:44.784
YOU KNOW WHY?
BECAUSE I CAN READ WOMEN.

03:44.820 --> 03:46.651
- AND SHE USED TO HAVE THAT
ON HER FACEBOOK PAGE.

03:46.690 --> 03:48.385
- WHICH I READ.

03:48.420 --> 03:49.648
EH, I THINK IT'S TIME
TO ROLL THE DICE.

03:49.690 --> 03:50.918
- [whistles]

03:50.960 --> 03:53.497
ORDER'S READY.

03:53.530 --> 03:56.294
AND SO IS TODAY'S QUESTION.

03:56.330 --> 03:58.662
- "HOW MANY TIMES
IS THE 'F' BOMB

03:58.700 --> 04:01.396
USED IN THE USUAL SUSPECT S?"

04:01.440 --> 04:03.328
WHOO!
MINKA.

04:03.370 --> 04:04.701
TAKING THINGS UP A NOTCH.

04:04.740 --> 04:07.277
THAT MIGHT ACTUALLY REQUIRE
A SIP OF COFFEE.

04:07.310 --> 04:08.675
- AH! AH!
NO GOOGLING.

04:08.710 --> 04:11.907
- DON'T INSULT MY INTELLIGENCE.

04:19.860 --> 04:21.953
- SHAWN?

04:21.990 --> 04:24.652
- AHEM.
97.

04:24.690 --> 04:27.693
- ACTUALLY, I BELIEVE IT'S 98.

04:27.730 --> 04:29.721
FENSTER DROPPED ONE AFI'ER
THAT LINEUP SCENE.

04:29.770 --> 04:31.965
OFTEN GETS MISTAKEN
FOR THE WORD "GUG,"

04:32.000 --> 04:33.661
WHICH ISN'T EVEN A WORD.

04:33.700 --> 04:35.292
BUT LET'S BE HONEST.
IT SHOULD BE.

04:35.340 --> 04:36.739
- WHAT'S HAPPENING RIGHT HERE?

04:36.770 --> 04:37.907
- HE'S RIGHT.
IT'S 98.

04:37.940 --> 04:38.907
- WHAT?

04:38.940 --> 04:40.874
- WHAT CAN I GET YOU?

04:40.910 --> 04:41.934
IT'S ON THE HOUSE.

04:41.980 --> 04:42.901
- OH, I'M ACTUALLY GOOD.

04:42.950 --> 04:47.319
I JUST CAME IN TO USE
YOUR RECYCLING BIN.

04:47.350 --> 04:50.786
- [stammers]

04:50.820 --> 04:55.712
WHO THE "GUG" IS THAT GUY?

04:55.760 --> 04:57.523
- THAT'LL BE $14.95.

05:05.400 --> 05:06.765
- I'M STILL ANNOYED, GUS.

05:06.800 --> 05:07.835
- WHO CARES ABOUT THE QUESTION?

05:07.870 --> 05:09.861
I CAN'T BELIEVE WE'RE WORKING
ON THE LORD'S DAY.

05:09.910 --> 05:11.366
- AND SUNDAY, FOR THAT MATTER.

05:11.410 --> 05:12.832
- SUNDAY IS THE LORD'S DAY,
SHAWN.

05:12.880 --> 05:15.701
LASSIE, I DIDN'T KNOW YOU WERE
PLAYING GOLF TODAY.

05:15.740 --> 05:17.378
- I WASN'T.

05:17.410 --> 05:18.809
- JULES, WHAT DO WE GOT?

05:18.850 --> 05:21.341
- LUCY FRIEDMAN,
70-YEAR-OLD FEMALE

05:21.380 --> 05:23.610
FOUND DEAD ON HER BLANKET AFTER
THE PHILHARMONIC LAST NIGHT,

05:23.650 --> 05:25.083
BUT SHE WASN'T DISCOVERED
UNTIL THIS MORNING.

05:26.560 --> 05:27.754
- I DO.
BOREDOM.

05:27.790 --> 05:28.916
- I LOVE THE PHILHARMONIC.

05:28.960 --> 05:30.621
- OH, ME TOO.
I'M JUST KIDDING.

05:30.660 --> 05:31.888
NOT.

05:31.930 --> 05:33.022
- STOP TRYING
TO SINGLE-HANDEDLY

05:33.060 --> 05:34.391
BRING "NOT" BACK INTO VOGUE.

05:34.430 --> 05:35.590
- OKAY.
NOT.

05:35.630 --> 05:37.063
I'M ALSO GONNA BRING BACK
"SAID THE LIAR."

05:37.100 --> 05:38.761
- THAT ONE IS EVEN DUMBER.
- SAID THE LIAR.

05:38.800 --> 05:40.939
- THERE'S NO VISIBLE MARKS
OR SIGNS OF A STRUGGLE.

05:40.970 --> 05:43.962
DOESN'T LOOK LIKE
FOUL PLAY TO ME.

05:52.050 --> 05:56.146
- OH, WHOA, LASSIE.
THE PSYCHIC GODS DISAGREE.

05:56.180 --> 05:57.784
I'M SENSING THAT THERE
IS A DIRECT LINK

05:57.820 --> 05:59.458
BETWEEN THIS POOR
WOMAN'S DEATH

05:59.490 --> 06:01.515
AND THE DEATHS
OF A PETER HODGES

06:01.560 --> 06:03.528
AND A VERONICA MILLER
EARLIER THIS WEEK.

06:03.560 --> 06:04.652
- AND WHAT LINK WOULD THAT BE?

06:04.690 --> 06:05.725
- ALL THREE DIED WITHIN
CLOSE PROXIMITY

06:05.760 --> 06:07.694
OF AN AEROSOL CAN.

06:07.730 --> 06:09.391
- ALL RIGHT, WHO ARE YOU?

06:09.430 --> 06:11.728
AND WHY DO YOU KEEP
STEALING MY MOMENTS?

06:11.770 --> 06:14.489
- I'M SORRY.
DECLAN RAND, CRIMINAL PROFILER.

06:14.540 --> 06:15.734
- RIGHT.

06:15.770 --> 06:17.601
CHIEF VICK SAID YOU'D
BE STOPPING BY.

06:17.640 --> 06:18.834
I'M DETECTIVE CARLTON LASSITER.

06:18.870 --> 06:20.838
THIS IS MY PARTNER
JULIET O'HARA AND...EH.

06:20.880 --> 06:22.905
- CRIMINAL PROFILER, HUH?

06:22.950 --> 06:24.679
SOUNDS LIKE ONE
OF THOSE JOB TITLES

06:24.710 --> 06:26.678
THAT ONLY EXISTS
IN CHEESY TV SHOWS.

06:26.720 --> 06:28.608
- NO ARGUMENT HERE.

06:28.650 --> 06:29.685
WHAT IS IT THAT YOU DO?

06:29.720 --> 06:30.744
- I'M A PSYCHIC DETECTIVE.

06:30.790 --> 06:31.814
- YOU KNOW WHAT?

06:31.850 --> 06:34.853
HE'S RIGHT ABOUT
THE AEROSOL CANS.

06:34.890 --> 06:36.528
HODGES DIED HOLDING A THING
OF VINYL PROTECT ANT

06:36.560 --> 06:39.597
AND MILLER WAS FOUND WITHIN FEET
OF A CAN OF HAIRSPRAY.

06:39.630 --> 06:40.824
- SO YOU'RE SAYING THIS IS
A SERIAL KILLER?

06:40.860 --> 06:43.863
- WELL, THE CONSISTENCIES
AT EACH SCENE

06:43.900 --> 06:45.697
COMBINED WITH THE CLOSE TIMING
OF THE DEATHS

06:45.730 --> 06:46.936
CERTAINLY MAKES IT
A POSSIBILITY.

06:46.970 --> 06:50.007
DEFINITELY RECOMMEND CHECKING
THE CONTENTS OF THOSE CANS.

06:50.040 --> 06:51.166
- I'M GONNA MAKE A CALL.

06:51.210 --> 06:52.199
- THANKS FOR THE TIP.
- OH, NO.

06:52.240 --> 06:53.673
IT'S MY PLEASURE, DETECTIVE.

06:53.710 --> 06:58.875
- WOW.

06:58.910 --> 07:00.775
WHY DON'T I LIKE THIS GUY?
- I DON'T KNOW.

07:00.820 --> 07:02.708
MAYBE 'CAUSE HE KEEPS
STEALING YOUR THUNDER.

07:02.750 --> 07:04.047
- BECAUSE HIS NAME IS "DECLAN."

07:04.090 --> 07:05.546
DON'T YOU FIND THAT
U'I'TERLY RIDICULOUS?

07:05.590 --> 07:06.784
- NO.

07:06.820 --> 07:07.787
- THAT'S BECAUSE
YOUR NAME'S "BURTON."

07:07.820 --> 07:08.912
- CAN WE GET OUT OF HERE?

07:08.960 --> 07:10.552
- NOT UNTIL I ASK JULES
TO BE MY DATE TO THE WEDDING.

07:10.590 --> 07:11.852
- NOW IS NOT THE TIME.
- WHY NOT?

07:11.890 --> 07:13.221
- WELL, FOR STARTERS,
THERE'S A DEAD BODY

07:13.260 --> 07:14.659
TEN YARDS AWAY.

07:14.700 --> 07:15.724
- DON'T BE SO OLD-FASHIONED.

07:15.760 --> 07:17.227
JULES?

07:17.270 --> 07:20.159
MAY I HAVE A WORD?

07:21.840 --> 07:25.105
- WELL, UH...

07:25.140 --> 07:26.732
I KNOW THIS IS TOTALLY
SHORT NOTICE,

07:26.780 --> 07:28.771
BUT I WAS WONDERING
IF, UH, UH,

07:28.810 --> 07:33.577
YOU'D LIKE TO BE MY DATE TO
A FRIEND'S WEDDING ON SATURDAY?

07:33.620 --> 07:36.214
- ARE YOU ASKING ME OUT NEXT
TO A DEAD PERSON?

07:36.250 --> 07:37.478
- TOLD YOU.
- YES.

07:37.520 --> 07:40.489
BUT I THOUGHT IT WOULD BE OKAY,
SINCE IT DOESN'T REALLY SMELL.

07:40.520 --> 07:41.953
- SATURDAY?

07:41.990 --> 07:44.254
UH, I WOULD LOVE TO...
- FANTASTIC.

07:44.290 --> 07:47.157
- BUT I LITERALLY JUST MADE
PLANS WITH SOMEONE ELSE.

07:47.200 --> 07:50.169
- WHAT?
WHO?

07:52.800 --> 07:53.960
OH, COME ON.

07:54.000 --> 07:56.707
- BUT IF I HAD KNOWN--
- NO.

07:56.740 --> 07:58.628
THAT'S FINE.

07:58.670 --> 07:59.773
- O'HARA, NEED YOU OVER HERE!

07:59.810 --> 08:02.745
- OKAY, UM, WELL, WE SHOULD TALK
ABOUT THIS LATER, YEAH?

08:02.780 --> 08:07.672
- YES, LATER.

08:07.720 --> 08:09.540
- HMM.

08:09.590 --> 08:11.717
- REALLY DON'T LIKE THE CUT
OF THAT GUY'S JIB, GUS.

08:11.750 --> 08:14.014
SOMETHING ABOUT HIM.
WHAT IS IT?

08:14.060 --> 08:16.278
- LET SEE.
HE'S SMART.

08:16.320 --> 08:17.878
KNOWLEDGEABLE OF FILM.

08:17.930 --> 08:19.693
CRIME-SOLVING MACHINE.

08:19.730 --> 08:21.823
HE'S SHAWN 2.0.

08:24.600 --> 08:27.569
[The Friendly Indians'
I Know You Know]

08:27.600 --> 08:30.899
*

08:30.940 --> 08:32.805
* IN BETWEEN THE LINES

08:32.840 --> 08:34.933
* THERE'S A LOT OF OBSCURITY

08:34.980 --> 08:38.279
* I'M NOT INCLINED
TO RESIGN TO MATURITY *

08:38.310 --> 08:40.039
* IF IT'S ALL RIGHT

08:40.080 --> 08:41.741
* THEN YOU'RE ALL WRONG

08:41.780 --> 08:46.285
* BUT WHY BOUNCE AROUND
TO THE SAME DAMN SONG? *

08:46.320 --> 08:50.780
* YOU'D RATHER RUN
BUT YOU CAN'T CRAWL *

08:50.830 --> 08:52.798
*

08:52.830 --> 08:54.092
* I KNOW YOU KNOW

08:54.130 --> 08:56.052
* THAT I'M NOT
TELLING THE TRUTH *

08:56.100 --> 08:57.692
* I KNOW YOU KNOW

08:57.730 --> 08:59.220
* THEY JUST DON'T HAVE
ANY PROOF *

08:59.270 --> 09:00.828
* EMBRACE THE DECEPTION

09:00.870 --> 09:02.701
* LEARN HOW TO BEND

09:02.740 --> 09:04.139
* YOUR WORST INHIBITION'S

09:04.170 --> 09:06.775
* GONNA PSYCH YOU OUT
IN THE END *

09:06.810 --> 09:09.870
*

09:14.250 --> 09:15.808
- I DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHY YOU'RE GIVING DECLAN

09:15.850 --> 09:17.317
ALL THE CREDIT FOR COMING UP
WITH THE FACT

09:17.350 --> 09:18.908
THAT THERE WAS POISON
IN THOSE CANS

09:18.950 --> 09:20.656
WHEN YOU KNOW I HAD
THE EXACT SAME TAKE.

09:20.690 --> 09:22.157
- SO WHY DIDN'T YOU
SAY ANYTHING?

09:22.190 --> 09:23.726
- BECAUSE HE BEAT ME
TO THE PUNCH, GUS.

09:23.760 --> 09:24.988
- JUST LIKE WITH JULIET
AND THE TRIVIA QUESTION.

09:25.030 --> 09:26.122
- YOU'RE A BIG, FAT PERSON.
- NO, I'M NOT.

09:26.160 --> 09:27.229
- I KNOW.

09:27.260 --> 09:27.954
I WAS TRYING TO GET YOU BACK
FOR MAKING ME FEEL BAD.

09:28.000 --> 09:31.367
- SHAWN, HEY.
- HEY, JULES!

09:31.400 --> 09:33.163
- WHY ARE YOU TALKING LIKE THAT?

09:33.200 --> 09:35.361
- SOMETIMES HE OVER-ENUNCIATES
WHEN HE GETS UNCOMFORTABLE.

09:35.400 --> 09:37.766
- I DO NOT.

09:37.810 --> 09:39.300
- CAN I TALK TO YOU
FOR A SECOND?

09:39.340 --> 09:42.070
- SURE.

09:42.110 --> 09:45.273
- UM, LISTEN,
ABOUT YESTERDAY,

09:45.310 --> 09:47.141
YOU KNOW,
I WAS THINKING ABOUT IT

09:47.180 --> 09:49.273
AND I BARELY KNOW DECLAN.

09:49.320 --> 09:51.788
I WILL RESCHEDULE WITH HIM
IF YOU REALLY NEED A DATE

09:51.820 --> 09:53.913
TO THIS WEDDING.
- [chuckles]

09:53.960 --> 09:56.622
NO, NO, JULES,
I DON'T NEED A DATE.

09:56.660 --> 09:58.127
I ONLY ASKED YOU THAT
'CAUSE I THOUGHT YOU MIGHT

09:58.160 --> 10:00.299
BE LOOKING FOR SOMETHING
TO DO THIS WEEKEND, YOU KNOW?

10:00.330 --> 10:02.992
FINDING ANOTHER DATE WILL BE
NO PROBLEM, TRUST ME.

10:03.030 --> 10:05.089
- OH, GOOD.

10:05.130 --> 10:08.236
I'M GLAD.
- YEAH.

10:08.270 --> 10:09.965
[sighs]

10:10.010 --> 10:11.762
DID YOU HEAR THAT?

10:11.810 --> 10:14.028
- EVERY ILL-CONCEIVED WORD.

10:14.080 --> 10:15.707
- NOW I HAVE TO FIND
A DATE TO THIS THING.

10:15.740 --> 10:16.968
- YEAH, YOU DO.

10:17.010 --> 10:18.739
- OKAY, LISTEN UP.

10:18.780 --> 10:20.645
IF YOU HAVEN'T HEARD ALREADY,

10:20.680 --> 10:22.784
WE HAVE A POTENTIAL
SERIAL KILLER ON THE LOOSE

10:22.820 --> 10:25.983
WHO HAS POISONED THREE VICTIMS
WITHIN FIVE DAYS.

10:26.020 --> 10:27.419
NOW, YOUR DEPARTMENT HEADS
WILL BRIEF YOU

10:27.460 --> 10:30.122
ON THE SPECIFICS, BUT WHAT
YOU NEED TO KNOW RIGHT NOW

10:30.160 --> 10:33.652
IS THAT EVERY OFFICER HERE
IS ON THIS CASE.

10:33.700 --> 10:36.919
ALL PRECINCT RESOURCES WILL
BE MADE AVAILABLE TO YOU,

10:36.970 --> 10:38.858
INCLUDING OUTSIDE CONSULTANTS.

10:38.900 --> 10:40.788
- SPECIFICALLY WE'LL
BE BRINGING IN PSYCH

10:40.840 --> 10:44.059
BECAUSE OF THEIR EXPERIENCE
WORKING WITH SERIAL KILLERS.

10:44.110 --> 10:46.908
- WE HELP THEM WRITE AND PRODUCE
ONE-ACT PLAYS ON THE WEEKENDS.

10:46.940 --> 10:48.009
- THEY'RE USUALLY VERY DARK.

10:48.040 --> 10:50.099
- WE'RE ALSO HIRING DECLAN RAND.

10:50.150 --> 10:51.845
- HELLO.

10:51.880 --> 10:54.178
- HIGHLY-TRAINED
CRIMINAL PROFILER

10:54.220 --> 10:56.017
WHO ALSO BROUGHT US OUR FIRST
BIG BREAK IN THE CASE.

10:56.050 --> 10:57.278
- YOU'VE GOT TO BE KIDDING ME.

10:57.320 --> 11:00.710
- HE'S GONNA SHARE WITH US HIS
INITIAL PROFILE OF THE SUSPECT.

11:00.760 --> 11:05.220
WE WILL NOT HAVE ANOTHER SERIAL
KILLER LOOSE ON OUR STREETS.

11:05.260 --> 11:06.227
- THANK YOU.
THANK YOU, KAREN.

11:06.260 --> 11:10.094
NOW, EACH OF THE VICTIMS
WAS KILLED BY HEMLOCK,

11:10.130 --> 11:13.429
A POISON THAT IN ADDITION
TO BEING A LOT OF FUN TO SAY--

11:13.470 --> 11:14.732
DON'T TAKE MY WORD FOR IT.
COME ON.

11:14.770 --> 11:17.000
all: HEMLOCK.

11:17.040 --> 11:18.928
- WORKS BY SLOWING SHU'I'TING DOWN
THE IMMUNE SYSTEM,

11:18.970 --> 11:20.198
CREATING AN ALMOST
PEACEFUL DEATH.

11:20.240 --> 11:21.935
- HEMLOCK.

11:21.980 --> 11:23.072
- AND GIVEN THAT THE VICTIMS
WERE ALL OVER THE AGE OF 60

11:23.110 --> 11:24.771
AND SUFFERING FROM
MAJOR ILLNESSES,

11:24.810 --> 11:27.142
I BELIEVE OUR KILLER COULD HAVE
EUTHANISTIC INTENTIONS.

11:27.180 --> 11:28.738
- YOU MEAN LIKE MERCY KILLINGS?

11:28.780 --> 11:30.111
- EXACTLY AND IT'S
MY ESTIMATION

11:30.150 --> 11:32.755
THEY WERE COMMITTED BY
A FEMALE IN HER MID-30$

11:32.790 --> 11:35.111
MOST LIKELY SUFFERING FROM AN
OVERWHELMING COMPASSIONATE SIDE.

11:35.160 --> 11:37.754
- I KNOW WHO IT IS.
- WHO?

11:37.790 --> 11:39.326
- ALICIA SILVERSTONE.

11:39.360 --> 11:41.055
BY THE WAY, DECLAN,
HER FIRST ROLE

11:41.100 --> 11:43.227
WAS IN THE MOVIE THE CRUSH.

11:43.270 --> 11:45.158
- ACTUALLY, THAT WAS HER
SECOND ROLE.

11:45.200 --> 11:47.339
SHE FIRST DID AN UNCREDITED
APPEARANCE IN THE WONDER YEARS.

11:47.370 --> 11:49.167
_ N--

11:49.200 --> 11:51.236
SHE DID.
HE'S RIGHT.

11:51.270 --> 11:54.000
HE'S GOOD.
- HEMLOCK.

11:54.040 --> 11:56.235
- OKAY, NOW THAT WE'VE GOT
THAT ALL CLEARED UP,

11:56.280 --> 11:59.249
LET'S GO OUT THERE
AND GET THIS GUY...OR GIRL.

12:09.960 --> 12:12.155
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING, SHAWN?

12:12.190 --> 12:14.192
- FIRST, YOU HIRE
TWO GERIATRIC COPS.

12:14.230 --> 12:16.050
FINE.
NOW YOU BRING IN THIS

12:16.100 --> 12:18.762
HACKY PROFILER WITH
THE WORLD'S WORST NAME

12:18.800 --> 12:20.495
AND THE MOST IMPOSSIBLY
DARK EYE LASHES

12:20.540 --> 12:21.893
ON ANY MAN EVER.
- HEMLOCK.

12:21.940 --> 12:22.838
- STOP IT.

12:22.870 --> 12:24.462
WHEN ARE YOU GONNA REALIZE
THAT GUS AND I

12:24.510 --> 12:25.534
ARE ALL YOU NEED?

12:25.570 --> 12:28.130
- ALL RIGHT, FIRST OF ALL,
I AGREE ABOUT THE NAME,

12:28.180 --> 12:30.444
BUT THIS GUY IS NOT
A HACK, SHAWN.

12:30.480 --> 12:32.209
I HAVE GOT GLOWING
RECOMMENDATIONS

12:32.250 --> 12:33.547
FROM TWO DIFFERENT
CHIEFS OF POLICE.

12:33.580 --> 12:35.241
CHECK OUT HIS RESUME.

12:35.280 --> 12:39.080
- HE HAS A MASTERS IN PSYCHOLOGY
AND CRIMINOLOGY FROM HARVARD

12:39.120 --> 12:40.348
AND AN MBA?
- GET OUT OF HERE.

12:40.390 --> 12:41.982
HE'S GOT A MONKEY
BASKETBALL LEAGUE?

12:42.020 --> 12:43.521
- SHAWN, THIS GUY IS GOOD.

12:43.560 --> 12:45.255
I HOPE YOU'RE UP
TO THE CHALLENGE.

12:45.290 --> 12:46.826
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
- OH, COME ON, KID.

12:46.860 --> 12:48.521
LET'S FACE IT.
YOU'VE BEEN SLOPPY LATELY.

12:48.560 --> 12:50.824
YOU'RE SHOWING UP AT CRIME
SCENES AFTER A LATE NIGHT OUT.

12:50.870 --> 12:52.019
- OR IN.

12:52.070 --> 12:55.437
- AND YOU MAILED IN THE LAST
CASE I GAVE YOU, LITERALLY.

12:55.470 --> 12:56.903
- MY EMAIL WAS DOWN.

12:56.940 --> 12:58.009
BESIDES, I WAS RIGHT,
WASN'T I?

12:58.040 --> 12:59.132
- IT DOESN'T MATTER.

12:59.170 --> 13:00.239
- HOW DOES THAT NOT MATTER?

13:00.280 --> 13:02.999
- THE POINT IS, IF YOU
WANT TO HANG WITH THIS GUY,

13:03.050 --> 13:04.301
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
TO UP YOUR GAME.

13:04.350 --> 13:06.170
- PLEASE.

13:06.210 --> 13:09.043
DECLAN RAND CAN'T TOUCH MY GAME.
YOU KNOW WHY?

13:09.080 --> 13:10.809
BECAUSE IT'S ON FIRE
AND IT'S COVERED

13:10.850 --> 13:14.149
WITH THOSE LITTLE THINGS
THAT PORCUPINES HAVE.

13:14.190 --> 13:15.179
- QUILLS.

13:15.220 --> 13:20.328
- YOU WATCH WHILE I SMOKE
THIS ARROGANT FOOL.

13:20.360 --> 13:22.897
- HEY, GUYS,
I JUST WANTED TO SAY

13:22.930 --> 13:25.069
I AM BLOWN AWAY
BY THE NUMBERS OF CASES

13:25.100 --> 13:26.124
YOU'VE SOLVED OVER THE YEARS.

13:26.170 --> 13:27.364
I JUST LOOKED IT UP.

13:27.400 --> 13:29.197
IT'S AN HONOR AND A PLEASURE
TO BE WORKING WITH BOTH OF YOU.

13:29.240 --> 13:30.502
- SOMEONE LIKES THEMSELVES.

13:30.540 --> 13:31.529
- THAN KS, DECLAN.

13:31.570 --> 13:33.470
- YEAH, MAN, I GOT TO BE HONEST.

13:33.510 --> 13:35.535
I'M JUST NOT A BIG BELIEVER
IN THE ABILITY

13:35.580 --> 13:38.071
TO PSYCHOLOGICALLY PROFILE
A COMPLETE STRANGER.

13:38.110 --> 13:39.577
- WELL, I RESPECT THAT,
BUT I DO IT SUCCESSFULLY

13:39.610 --> 13:41.077
ALL THE TIME.

13:41.120 --> 13:42.246
- REALLY?
[chuckles]

13:42.280 --> 13:43.542
TRY ME.

13:43.590 --> 13:45.080
- I'D REALLY PREFER NOT TO.

13:45.120 --> 13:46.018
- BECAUSE YOU CAN'T.

13:46.050 --> 13:48.484
- WELL, THE TRUTH IS I--
- YOU'RE NOT ABLE.

13:48.520 --> 13:52.024
- YOU'RE HIGHLY INTELLIGENT,
BUT YOU'RE SHAMEFUL

13:52.060 --> 13:53.527
OF THAT FACT,
SO YOU PLAY IT DOWN

13:53.560 --> 13:55.255
WITH THE USE
OF INAPPROPRIATE BEHAVIOR,

13:55.300 --> 13:57.268
AND YOU LIVE IN FEAR
OF SHOWING WEAKNESS

13:57.300 --> 14:00.064
SO YOU HIDE BEHIND A CONSTANT
BARRAGE OF JOKES AND SARCASM.

14:00.100 --> 14:02.568
- I AGREE.

14:02.600 --> 14:05.160
NOT.
SAID THE LIAR.

14:05.210 --> 14:07.337
- NOT SURE THOSE TWO
GO TOGETHER.

14:07.380 --> 14:08.972
"SAID THE LIAR"
CANCELS "NOT" OUT.

14:09.010 --> 14:11.547
- SO DOES YOUR FACE.

14:11.580 --> 14:13.138
WHAT ELSE?

14:13.180 --> 14:15.375
- I'VE NOTICED YOU OVERLY
ENUNCIATE WORDS AT TIMES,

14:15.420 --> 14:18.218
WHICH I SUSPECT IS SOME
KIND OF NERVOUS REACTION

14:18.250 --> 14:19.615
TO CONFRONTATION
OR AWKWARDNESS.

14:19.650 --> 14:22.619
- YEAH.
COULDN'T BE FURTHER OFF.

14:25.960 --> 14:29.088
- TAKE CARE.

14:29.130 --> 14:30.563
- HE WASN'T OFF.

14:30.600 --> 14:32.898
- I KNOW.

14:32.940 --> 14:34.999
- AS YOU CAN SEE, WE HAVE
THE BODY OF OUR VICTIM

14:35.040 --> 14:36.064
FROM THE PARK RIGHT HERE.

14:36.100 --> 14:39.638
AND RIGHT HERE WE HAVE
MS. MILLER AND MR. HODGES.

14:39.670 --> 14:41.308
- WHAT ABOUT THAT ONE?

14:41.340 --> 14:44.548
- OH, THAT'S A PHOTO MY
15-YEAR-OLD DAUGHTER'S TAKEN

14:44.580 --> 14:46.241
FOR HER PHOTOGRAPHY CLASS.

14:46.280 --> 14:47.645
- IS THAT DEAD PERSON YOU?

14:47.680 --> 14:49.238
- VERY OBSERVANT.
YES.

14:49.280 --> 14:51.145
IT'S AMAZING WHAT JUST A--
REALLY--

14:51.190 --> 14:53.283
A LITTLE KETCHUP
AND BABY POWDER CAN DO.

14:53.320 --> 14:57.154
ANYWAY, I THINK THAT I AGREE
WITH DECLAN'S THEORY

14:57.190 --> 14:59.226
THAT TH ESE ARE ALL MERCY
KILLINGS.

14:59.260 --> 15:01.148
- WHAT?
LOOK, WOODY,

15:01.200 --> 15:03.191
WE'RE JUST LOOKING
FOR THE FACTS HERE.

15:03.230 --> 15:04.197
- SINCE WHEN?

15:04.230 --> 15:05.492
- YOU SEE, EACH OF THESE VICTIMS

15:05.530 --> 15:07.066
WAS SUFFERING FROM
A LIFE-THREATENING DISEASE.

15:07.100 --> 15:09.398
CIRRHOSIS AND ADVANCED
HEPATITIS, RESPECT IVELY,

15:09.440 --> 15:11.658
AND MRS. FRIEDMAN HERE WAS
SUFFERING FROM WILSON'S DISEASE.

15:11.710 --> 15:14.235
- WILSON'S DISEASE?

15:14.280 --> 15:16.168
- "YOUR PATIENT DYING
OF WILSON'S DISEASE

15:16.210 --> 15:17.700
IS GOING TO GET A LIVER
FROM THE DONOR LIST,"

15:17.750 --> 15:19.308
EXCLAIMED CHASE.

15:19.350 --> 15:21.944
EDEN WAS ECSTATIC.

15:21.980 --> 15:23.538
"BUT IF I DO THE SURGERY,
THE BLOOD LOSS

15:23.590 --> 15:25.444
"WILL BE ENORMOUS,
BECAUSE I WILL MOST LIKELY

15:25.490 --> 15:27.458
DRINK HALF OF IT."

15:27.490 --> 15:29.185
EDEN WAS IN A BIND.

15:29.220 --> 15:30.687
- YEAH, SHE WAS.

15:30.730 --> 15:32.220
YOU ARE NEVER ALLOWED
TO MOCK ME

15:32.260 --> 15:33.295
FOR LISTENING
TO THOSE BOOKS AGAIN.

15:33.330 --> 15:34.319
I'M GETTING SOMETHING.

15:34.360 --> 15:35.349
- WHAT IS IT?

15:35.400 --> 15:39.427
- THOSE WERE NOT MERCY KILLINGS.

15:46.570 --> 15:48.435
- I DON'T KNOW WHAT
IN SAM'S HELL THIS HAS TO DO

15:48.480 --> 15:49.708
WITH A TRANSPLANT LIST,
BUT I'M FAIRLY CERTAIN

15:49.740 --> 15:51.401
IT'S A WASTE OF TIME.

15:51.450 --> 15:53.441
- I SAY WE TRUST SHAWN'S
INSTINCTS ON THIS ONE.

15:53.480 --> 15:54.617
- SAID THE LIAR.

15:54.650 --> 15:56.140
- HE WAS SUPPORTING YOU.

15:56.180 --> 15:57.716
- REALLY?
I JUMPED THE GUN.

15:57.750 --> 15:59.240
- EXCUSE ME, DETECTIVE?

15:59.290 --> 16:02.111
I BELIEVE THIS IS WHAT YOU
WERE ASKING FOR.

16:02.160 --> 16:03.752
IT'S A LIST OF ALL
OF THE PEOPLE IN THE AREA

16:03.790 --> 16:05.280
WAITING FOR A LIVER TRANSPLANT.

16:05.330 --> 16:07.252
- OH, CRAP.
- WHAT?

16:07.300 --> 16:09.518
- LOOK AT THE FIRST THREE NAMES.

16:09.560 --> 16:12.768
- PETER HODGES, VERONICA MILLER,
LUCY FRIEDMAN.

16:12.800 --> 16:14.165
- SOMEONE COULD
BE KILLING PEOPLE OFF

16:14.200 --> 16:15.189
TO MOVE UP THE LIST.

16:15.240 --> 16:16.264
- EXACTLY.

16:16.300 --> 16:17.528
NICE TRY THOUGH, BUDDY.

16:17.570 --> 16:19.265
- HMM.

16:19.310 --> 16:21.278
JUST OUT OF CURIOSITY,
WHO'S THE NEXT PERSON IN LINE?

16:21.310 --> 16:23.278
- CATHERINE BICKS.

16:23.310 --> 16:25.574
- AGE?
- 35.

16:25.610 --> 16:28.374
SHE TOTALLY MATCHES
YOUR PROFILE.

16:28.420 --> 16:30.411
- WELL DONE, DECLAN.

16:30.450 --> 16:32.213
- "WELL DONE, DECLAN"?

16:32.250 --> 16:34.115
SINCE WHEN DO YOU USE
FIRST NAMES?

16:34.160 --> 16:35.218
- WE NEED TO TRACK
THIS GIRL DOWN.

16:35.260 --> 16:37.728
- HEY, I'M THE ONE THAT CAME UP
WITH THE LIST THING.

16:37.760 --> 16:39.284
- GOOD WORK, SHAWN.

16:39.330 --> 16:42.026
- SHUT UP, DECLAN.

16:46.700 --> 16:50.158
- KRISTA, HEY.
SHAWN SPENCER HERE.

16:50.210 --> 16:53.600
YES, I AM THE ONE THAT TOOK YOU
TO THAT DODGERS GAME.

16:53.640 --> 16:55.198
OH, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.
BACK UP.

16:55.240 --> 16:56.275
I DID NOT RUN ONTO THE FIELD.

16:56.310 --> 16:59.507
I MERELY TOOK A FEW STEPS
TO FOLLOW A FOUL BALL.

16:59.550 --> 17:02.439
ENDED UP IN CENTER FIELD AFTER
IT RICOCHETED OFF A DIVIDER

17:02.480 --> 17:05.483
WHERE I PROCEEDED TO MAKE LIKE
BILLY "WHITE SHOES" JOHNSON.

17:05.520 --> 17:07.556
I REALIZE THAT REFERENCE
IS LOST ON YOU.

17:07.590 --> 17:10.479
WHAT ARE YOU DOING ON SATURDAY?

17:10.530 --> 17:12.259
HELLO?

17:12.290 --> 17:14.224
- PLEASE TELL ME YOU DID NOT
SLEEP HERE AGAIN LAST NIGHT.

17:14.260 --> 17:15.557
- NOPE.

17:15.600 --> 17:17.727
GOT HERE HALF AN HOUR AGO
TO GET STUFF DONE.

17:17.770 --> 17:19.328
WHAT?

17:19.370 --> 17:21.292
TRIED TO MAKE SOME JOE,
BUT OUR COFFEE MAKER'S BUSTED.

17:21.340 --> 17:22.591
- WE DON'T HAVE A COFFEE MAKER.

17:22.640 --> 17:23.834
- WHAT WAS I FIDDLING WITH
FOR THE LAST HALF HOUR?

17:23.870 --> 17:25.269
- WHAT IS ALL THAT?

17:25.310 --> 17:26.538
- THIS?
THIS RIGHT HERE?

17:26.570 --> 17:29.175
THIS IS RESEARCH I DUG UP
ON ALL THE PEOPLE

17:29.210 --> 17:30.302
THAT MAKE UP
THE TRANSPLANT LIST.

17:30.350 --> 17:31.772
- HMM.

17:31.810 --> 17:34.370
I GOT TO SAY, SHAWN,
THIS IS PRETTY IMPRESSIVE.

17:34.420 --> 17:35.444
- MM-HMM.

17:35.480 --> 17:36.640
- I GUESS YOUR DAD SHOULD
HIRE RINGERS MORE OFTEN.

17:36.680 --> 17:37.783
- TRUST ME ON THIS.

17:37.820 --> 17:39.617
DECLAN IS NO RINGER.

17:39.650 --> 17:42.551
ONCE I'VE PROVED THAT THE KILLER
IS SOMEONE ON THIS LIST

17:42.590 --> 17:44.649
NOT NAMED CATHERINE BICKS,
EVERYONE,

17:44.690 --> 17:46.282
INCLUDING JULIET,
WILL REALIZE THAT.

17:46.330 --> 17:47.524
- OKAY, I GET IT.

17:47.560 --> 17:48.720
SO YOU FIGURE IF YOU CAN WIN
THIS CASE,

17:48.760 --> 17:50.193
THEN YOU'LL WIN JULIET.

17:50.230 --> 17:52.095
- NO, BUT IF MAKING DECLAN
LOOK SUCKY

17:52.130 --> 17:55.167
SOMEHOW DIMINISHES HIS APPEAL
IN JULIET'S EYES, I'LL TAKE IT.

17:55.200 --> 17:56.667
LOOK, GUS, THIS ISN'T PERSONAL.

17:56.700 --> 17:58.634
- YOU DO REALIZE EVERYTHING
YOU JUST SAID

17:58.670 --> 17:59.864
IS THE DEFINITION
OF "PERSONAL," RIGHT?

17:59.910 --> 18:01.798
- NOT.

18:01.840 --> 18:04.741
[cell phone rings]

18:04.780 --> 18:06.509
HELLO, DAD.

18:06.550 --> 18:08.415
- CATHERINE BICKS WAS SPOTTED
ENTERING HER HOUSE

18:08.450 --> 18:09.371
ABOUT AN HOUR AGO.

18:09.420 --> 18:13.481
YOU TWO HAVE TO GET
OVER THERE IMMEDIATELY.

18:13.520 --> 18:15.511
SHAWN?

18:15.560 --> 18:16.618
ARE YOU LISTENING TO ME?

18:16.660 --> 18:20.494
- MY HUMIDIFIER LOOKS
NOTHING LIKE A COFFEE MAKER.

18:20.530 --> 18:23.226
- I'LL BUY YOU A NEW ONE.

18:29.170 --> 18:31.161
- TO CATHERINE, SHE WAS
JUSTIFIED IN KILLING

18:31.210 --> 18:32.563
THE PEOPLE AHEAD OF HER
ON THAT LIST

18:32.610 --> 18:35.579
BECAUSE UNLIKE THEM, SHE HAS
ENTIRE LIFE AHEAD OF HER.

18:35.610 --> 18:37.601
WE CALL IT SOCIOPATHIC
RATIONALIZATION.

18:37.650 --> 18:39.572
- UGH, I FIND THAT
STUFF FASCINATING.

18:39.610 --> 18:41.578
- ME TOO.
- DON'T SAY, "NOT."

18:41.620 --> 18:43.508
NONE OF THOSE STUPID EXPRESSIONS
ARE COMING BACK.

18:43.550 --> 18:44.585
- THAT'S WHAT THEY SAID ABOUT
HAMMER PANTS.

18:44.620 --> 18:45.712
- WHICH NEVER CAME BACK.

18:45.750 --> 18:47.411
- THEN WHY DID I JUST
BUY THREE PAIR?

18:47.460 --> 18:49.348
- BECAUSE YOU'RE AN IDIOT.
- BECAUSE IT'S HAMMER TIME.

18:49.390 --> 18:50.550
- IT'S NEVER HAMMER TIME, SHAWN.

18:50.590 --> 18:54.856
- DARE YOU TO TELL HAMMER THAT.

18:54.900 --> 18:56.492
- CAN I HELP YOU?

18:56.530 --> 18:57.758
- CATHERINE BICKS,
WE'D LIKE TO ASK YOU

18:57.800 --> 19:00.496
A FEW QUESTIONS ABOUT A RECENT
STRING OF MURDERS IN THIS AREA.

19:00.540 --> 19:02.667
- WOW.

19:02.700 --> 19:06.409
OKAY, COME ON IN.

19:06.440 --> 19:08.408
I'M NOT A SUSPECT, AM I?

19:08.440 --> 19:12.342
- I DON'T KNOW.
SHOULD YOU BE?

19:12.380 --> 19:13.779
- [stammering]

19:13.820 --> 19:15.469
LISTEN, I DON'T KNOW WHAT'S
GOING ON HERE, BUT I--

19:15.520 --> 19:16.748
- MA'AM, PLEASE KEEP YOUR HANDS
WHERE I CAN SEE THEM.

19:16.780 --> 19:18.213
- NO, I JUST NEED TO GRAB--

19:18.250 --> 19:21.617
- PUT YOUR HANDS
IN THE AIR NOW!

19:31.570 --> 19:34.391
- CATHERINE, HI.

19:34.440 --> 19:36.533
I'M SENSING THAT YOU RECENTLY
SPENT SOME TIME

19:36.570 --> 19:37.969
IN SWITZERLAND.
IS THAT CORRECT?

19:38.010 --> 19:39.466
- YEAH.

19:39.510 --> 19:41.671
I WAS VISITING MY LIVER
SPECIALIST THERE.

19:41.710 --> 19:43.644
- MM-HMM.
GOOD TWO WEEKS OR SO?

19:43.680 --> 19:44.669
- 2 1/2.

19:44.710 --> 19:46.246
- YOU CAN PROVE THAT?

19:46.280 --> 19:48.316
- MY PASSPORT'S IN MY PURSE.

19:48.350 --> 19:49.510
THAT'S WHAT I WAS REACHING
FOR BEFORE HE PULLED

19:49.550 --> 19:52.747
THIS GIANT GUN OUT AT ME.

19:52.790 --> 19:55.714
- IT'S STAMPED.

19:59.630 --> 20:01.325
- CATHERINE, I AM SO SORRY.

20:01.360 --> 20:04.568
UM, YOU HAVE YOURSELF
A GREAT DAY, OKAY?

20:08.040 --> 20:10.565
- [coughs]
OOPS.

20:10.610 --> 20:11.838
YOU PLAY SOFTBALL?

20:11.870 --> 20:14.373
I PLAY.

20:14.410 --> 20:15.672
FEELS FUN.

20:15.710 --> 20:17.473
THIS IS PROBABLY
A WEIRD TIME TO ASK,

20:17.510 --> 20:20.513
BUT DO YOU HAVE PLANS
ON SATURDAY?

20:20.550 --> 20:22.518
- ARE YOU SURE WE DON'T WANT
TO ASK HER MORE QUESTIONS?

20:22.550 --> 20:24.586
SHE WAS A PRECISE MATCH
IN MY PROFILE.

20:24.620 --> 20:26.815
- YOUR PROFILE CAN KISS MY BIG,
ROUND, WHITE DUMPER, DECLAN.

20:26.850 --> 20:28.886
I DO NOT ENJOY POINTING
MY GUN AT INNOCENT WOMEN.

20:28.920 --> 20:30.729
- YOU DON'T?
- NO.

20:30.760 --> 20:31.988
I'M NOT 29 ANYMORE.

20:32.030 --> 20:33.554
- IT WAS A GOOD EFFORT, DECK.

20:33.600 --> 20:34.692
- I GUESS WE SHOULD CHECK
THE NEXT PERSON

20:34.730 --> 20:35.492
ON THE TRANSPLANT LIST.

20:35.530 --> 20:38.897
- YEAH, THAT IS
A LEONARD JIMENEZ.

20:38.930 --> 20:40.693
HE LIVES AT 19 WILLOW STREET.
THAT'S 10 MINUTES FROM HERE.

20:40.740 --> 20:42.628
- LET'S GO.

20:42.670 --> 20:45.730
- GUS AND I WILL MEET YOU THERE.

20:51.980 --> 20:53.641
- WHY THE HELL ARE WE
AT A HOTEL?

20:53.680 --> 20:56.774
- BECAUSE LEONARD JIMENEZ DIED
OF LIVER CANCER THREE DAYS AGO.

20:56.820 --> 20:58.640
I LEARNED THAT IN MY RESEARCH
THIS MORNING.

20:58.690 --> 21:01.318
- SO WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL THAT
TO LASSITER AND JULIET?

21:01.360 --> 21:02.884
- MUST HAVE SLIPPED
MY MIND, GUS.

21:02.920 --> 21:05.354
LOOK, IN THE HOUR OR SO IT TAKES
THEM TO PUT IT TOGETHER,

21:05.390 --> 21:07.426
